<span id="freeTextContainer3333849200481650242">This just isn&apos;t very good. After a promising and creepy opening, it devolves into repetitive ridiculousness. The writing is also just not good and sometimes laughable, providing such gems as this:<br/><br/>&quot;Eph too had been turned. Not from human to vampire, but from healer to slayer.&quot;<br/><br/>I did somehow finish it. My wife did not. I&apos;m sure del Toro will eventually make a movie out of this and it will be one of the rare occasions that the movie is better than the book.</span>
  <span id="freeText3333849200481650242" style="display:none">This just isn't very good. After a promising and creepy opening, it devolves into repetitive ridiculousness. The writing is also just not good and sometimes laughable, providing such gems as this:<br /><br />"Eph too had been turned. Not from human to vampire, but from healer to slayer."<br /><br />I did somehow finish it. My wife did not. I'm sure del Toro will eventually make a movie out of this and it will be one of the rare occasions that the movie is better than the book.</span>
