<span id="freeTextContainer16475128092096978124">Heck yes!! This book was legit the perfect combination of action, suspense, science fiction, horror, drama, it had it all!! I&apos;ve been a huge fan of the TV series for a long time now and decided to re-watch the entire series during the month of October, which got me wondering how the novels read in comparison. I will say that book one covered about half of the first season, but it read very much the same as the show and there weren&apos;t really any changes that I noticed, so it will be very interesti</span>
  <span id="freeText16475128092096978124" style="display:none">Heck yes!! This book was legit the perfect combination of action, suspense, science fiction, horror, drama, it had it all!! I've been a huge fan of the TV series for a long time now and decided to re-watch the entire series during the month of October, which got me wondering how the novels read in comparison. I will say that book one covered about half of the first season, but it read very much the same as the show and there weren't really any changes that I noticed, so it will be very interesting to see how the remaining two books compare to the remaining seasons of the TV series (or vice versa)! I'd definitely recommend this to any fellow horror/vampire fan, with caution as it is incredibly gory and not for the faint of heart!</span>
